<h2>Building an Online Store in Kenya: What You Need to Know</h2>
<p>E-commerce in Kenya is growing fast. With over 22 million internet users and M-Pesa deeply embedded in daily commerce, the infrastructure for online selling has never been more ready. If you sell physical products, digital goods, or services with a fixed price, an online store can turn your website into a revenue machine — open 24 hours, seven days a week.</p>
<p>This guide covers everything you need to build an e-commerce website in Kenya: platform choices, payment setup, costs, and what actually drives sales.</p>

<h2>E-commerce Platforms Available in Kenya</h2>
<h3>WooCommerce (WordPress)</h3>
<p>The most widely used e-commerce platform in Kenya. It's built on WordPress and allows you to sell any type of product with extensive customisation. Good for: businesses with large, complex catalogues. Watch out for: slow performance, plugin conflicts, and ongoing maintenance costs.</p>

<h3>Shopify</h3>
<p>A hosted e-commerce platform with a monthly fee (USD 29–299/month). Easy to set up and manage. The main challenge in Kenya is payment integration — Shopify doesn't natively support M-Pesa, and third-party M-Pesa gateways add cost and complexity.</p>

<h3>Custom-Built E-commerce</h3>
<p>A purpose-built online store coded specifically for your business. Higher upfront cost, but faster, more secure, and with native M-Pesa integration from the start. Best for: businesses with specific UX requirements or high-volume sales. This is what Tupate Studio builds.</p>

<h2>M-Pesa Integration: The Kenya-Specific Requirement</h2>
<p>In Kenya, M-Pesa is not optional. The majority of online purchases are completed via M-Pesa — particularly on mobile. There are two main ways to accept M-Pesa on your website:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>M-Pesa STK Push (Lipa na M-Pesa Online)</strong> — the customer enters their phone number and is prompted to confirm payment on their phone. Seamless, native experience.</li>
  <li><strong>M-Pesa Paybill / Buy Goods</strong> — the customer manually sends money to your Paybill/Till number. Less seamless, higher drop-off rate.</li>
</ul>
<p>STK Push via the Daraja API is the gold standard for Kenyan e-commerce. At Tupate Studio, we integrate M-Pesa Daraja into every online store we build.</p>

