<h2>What Makes Kenyan Customers Buy Online?</h2>
<p>Trust is the biggest barrier to e-commerce adoption in Kenya. Customers need to believe they'll receive what they pay for. Build trust with:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Clear delivery policy</strong> — areas covered, timelines, and costs</li>
  <li><strong>Returns policy</strong> — what happens if the product is wrong or damaged</li>
  <li><strong>Real contact details</strong> — phone number, WhatsApp, physical address</li>
  <li><strong>Customer reviews</strong> — genuine testimonials with names and photos</li>
  <li><strong>Secure checkout</strong> — HTTPS, recognisable payment brands (M-Pesa, Visa, Mastercard)</li>
  <li><strong>Order tracking</strong> — even a simple "your order has been confirmed" WhatsApp message significantly reduces buyer anxiety</li>
</ul>

